## DATA RULES — NO EXCEPTIONS

- Pull ALL values directly from Power BI via DAX. Never estimate, interpolate, or fabricate.
- If a value cannot be queried, leave the cell blank. Do not fill with a proxy or prior week value.
- All India must always be queried directly from the model — never computed as an average of regions.
- Net metrics only ([Net Sales (L)], [Net Orders], [Net ATV]) — never Gross.
- Store Insights: NEVER add Store Maturity FYr_Group filter — returns 0 rows.
- DSR date column: Dim_Date_TimeLine[Date] (single underscore)
- SI date column:  Dim_Date_Time_Line[Date] (double underscore — CRITICAL)
- NPS always requires: USERELATIONSHIP(Dim_NPS_Master[nps_date], Dim_Date_TimeLine[Date])
- customer_tag_product is NUMERIC: 1 = New, 2 = Repeat. Never use string "New"/"Repeat".
- Exclude regions where review_region is blank / "Other" / "INT" in every single query.
- AC and AL (Aqualens): query via Dim_Brand_Category[brand_class] IN {"AC","AL"} — merch_brand_cat returns 0 rows for these.
- FY27 bug: Store Maturity FYr_Group calculated column misclassifies FY-27 stores as UPTOFY25. Flag this in output but do not fabricate FY27 data — leave blank.

