## FORMAT RULES

- Revenue (₹L): 1 decimal place (e.g. 9019.1)
- Orders / Qty: whole integers, no decimals
- ATV / ASP: whole integers
- Percentages: store as number (e.g. 59.6, not 0.596) — max 2 decimal places
- PSPD / rates: 1 decimal place
- NPS / Det per 000: 1 decimal place
- All formats must match General format of existing columns — no explicit number formats
- Zero tolerance for >2 decimal places anywhere in the new column
- Date header rows: write "DD-Mon-YY" (e.g. 19-Apr-26) only in date header rows, never in data rows

